message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a novel deep convolutional neural network method for synthetic CT generation from MR images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the method is in the field of medical imaging (cs.MED) and specifically in radiotherapy. The use of deep learning and neural networks also suggests a possible fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of transfer learning and the large number of free parameters in the model, which are common themes in the neural network and deep learning literature, suggesting a possible fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) category.
